  "title": "wt remove and picker-driven removal: data-loss surface",
  "summary": "Worktree removal is the highest-stakes destructive operation. Force-remove must require explicit user consent; cleanup must not silently discard uncommitted changes or untracked files. Race conditions between safety checks and the actual delete must fail closed (retain data). The picker also routes alt-r through handle_remove_output - must consult approvals read-only and skip rather than prompt mid-render. See CLAUDE.md > Data Safety, Time-of-check vs time-of-use.",
